spanGrp.span: ‘A man and a woman have a child.
E-gla pekaga jemẽ pemina rö yaba ta e-gla
He then went to work and the woman stayed at home doing things.
Jekepa í kaga mẽnẽu-mĩ shkablö í mina jatanã jirö wã jũ ska
The woman left and let the child at home,
Í mina mẽnẽu-te í jatanã' jũ ska
and suddenly two coatis appeared, which scared the child off.
ñerö je_jueta bo-l (_) sirak desãu-lo í wömĩ je të yaba mẽlechá-wã
He then came down from where his mother had put him.
jẽk jáwã-te mãĩ mina të játanã köpö ska
The coatis ran away and the child ran after them.
Sirak julunã' tulá-mĩ jekepa yaba yulei të í töjiáu-mĩ (_) mẽnẽu-mĩ bo-l sirak-wa töinga
When he lost track of them, he fell on a huge snake;
Demĩũ demĩũ í shká jela shká kepa kuando ya sirak shenã' í wömĩ kepa í janãka mãĩ kebé keyege kablali bata inga
the snake grabbed him and he fell down again.
At that point something big and black came by;
jueta mãĩ jirö deũ dolonã keyege të je ra
His parents were looking for him;
Í kaga mina damĩũ-lo-mĩ í yulö
they fought against another creature but could not find the child.’
Jeska í ña bá-nẽ e-gla bichi deũ kwãwa je ra ka ĩã í yaba ka í yaba konẽ
